\cl CHAP.
\c 1
\iex 1 Adams line to Noah. 5 The sonnes of Iapheth. 8 The sonnes of Ham. 17 The sonnes of Shem. 24 Shems line to Abraham. 29 Ishmaels sonnes. 32 The sonnes of Keturah. 34 The posteritie of Abraham by Esau. 43 The Kings of Edom. 51 The Dukes of Edom.
\v 1 ¶ Adam, \x + \xo 1:1 \xt Gen. 5.3,9.\x*Sheth, Enosh,
\v 2 Kenan, Mahalaleel, Iered,
\v 3 Henoch, Methushelah, Lamech,
\v 4 Noah, Shem, Ham, & Iapheth.
\v 5 ¶ \x + \xo 1:5 \xt Gen. 10.2\x*The sonnes of Iapheth: Gomer, and Magog, and Madai, and Iauan, and Tubal, and Meshech, and Tiras.
\v 6 And the sonnes of Gomer: Ashchenaz, and \f + \fr 1:6 \ft Or, Diphath, as it is in some copies.\f*Riphath, and Togarmah.
\v 7 And the sonnes of Iauan: Elishah, and Tarshish, Kittim, and \f + \fr 1:7 \ft Or, Rodanim, accorning to some copies.\f*Dodanim.
\v 8 ¶ The sonnes of Ham: Cush, and Mizraim, Put, and Canaan.
\v 9 And the sonnes of Cush: Siba, and Hauilah, and Sabta, and Raamah, and Sabtecha: and the sonnes of Raamah: Sheba, and Dedan.
\v 10 And Cush \x + \xo 1:10 \xt Gen. 10.8.\x*begate Nimrod: hee began to be mightie vpon the earth.
\v 11 And Mizraim begate Ludim, and Anamim, and Lehabim, and Naphtuhim,
\v 12 And Pathrusim, and Casluhim (of whome came the Philistines) and \x + \xo 1:12 \xt Deut. 2.23.\x*Caphthorim.
\v 13 And Canaan begate Zidon his first borne, and Heth.
\v 14 The Iebusite also, and the Amorite, and the Girgashite,
\v 15 And the Hiuite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite,
\v 16 And the Aruadite, and the Zemarite, and the Hamathite.
\v 17 ¶ The sonnes of \x + \xo 1:17 \xt Gen. 10.23. & 11.10.\x*Shem: Elam, and Asshur, and Arphaxad, and Lud, and Aram, and Uz, & Hul, and Gether, and \x + \xo 1:17 \xt Or, Mash. gen. 10.23.\x*Meshech.
\v 18 And Arphaxad begate Shelah, and Shelah begate Eber.
\v 19 And vnto Eber were borne two sonnes: the name of the one \add was\add* \f + \fr 1:19 \ft That is division.\f*Peleg, (because in his dayes the earth \add was\add* diuided) and his brothers name was Ioktan.
\v 20 And \x + \xo 1:20 \xt Gen. 10.26.\x*Ioktan begate Almodad, and Sheleph, and Hazermaueth, and Ierah,
\v 21 Hadoram also, and Uzal, and Diklah,
\v 22 And Ebal, and Abimael, and Sheba,
\v 23 And Ophir, and Hauilah, and Iobab: all these \add were\add* the sonnes of Ioktan.
\v 24 ¶ \x + \xo 1:24 \xt Luke 3.24.\x*Shem, Arphaxad, Shelah,
\v 25 \x + \xo 1:25 \xt Gen. 11.15.\x*Eber, Peleg, Rehu,
\v 26 Serug, Nahor, Terah,
\v 27 \x + \xo 1:27 \xt Gen. 17.5.\x*Abram, the same \add is\add* Abraham.
\v 28 The sonnes of Abraham: \x + \xo 1:28 \xt Gen. 21.2,3.\x*Isaac, and \x + \xo 1:28 \xt Gen.16.11.\x*Ishmael.
\v 29 ¶ These \add are\add* their generations: The \x + \xo 1:29 \xt Gen. 25.13, to 17.\x*first-borne of Ishmael, Nebaioth, then Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,
\v 30 Mishma, and Dumah, Massa, \x + \xo 1:30 \xt Or, Hadar, Gen. 25.14.\x*Hadad, and Tema,
\v 31 Ietur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sonnes of Ishmael.
\v 32 ¶ Now the sonnes of Keturah, Abrahams Concubine: she bare Zimran, and Iokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah. And the sonnes of Iokshan, Sheba, and Dedan.
\v 33 And the sonnes of Midian: Ephah, and Ephar, and Henoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these \add are\add* the sonnes of Keturah.
\v 34 And Abraham begate Isaac. The sonnes of Isaac: Esau, and Israel.
\v 35 ¶ The sonnes of \x + \xo 1:35 \xt Gen. 36.9,10.\x*Esau: Eliphaz, Reuel, and Ieush, and Iaalam, and Korah.
\v 36 The sonnes of Eliphaz: Teman, and Omar, \x + \xo 1:36 \xt Or, Zepho, Gen. 36.12.\x*Zephi, and Gatam, Kenaz, and Timna, and Amalek.
\v 37 The sonnes of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.
\v 38 And the sonnes of Seir: Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah, and Dishon, and Ezer, and Dishan.
\v 39 And the sonnes of Lotan: Hori, and \x + \xo 1:39 \xt Or, Heman, Gen. 36.22.\x*Homam: and Timna \add was\add* Lotans sister.
\v 40 The sonnes of Shobal: \x + \xo 1:40 \xt Or, Aluan, Gen 36.23.\x*Atian, and Manahath, and Ebal, \x + \xo 1:40 \xt Or, Sepho, Gen. 36.23.\x*Shephi, and Onam. And the sonnes of Zibeon: Aiah, and Anah.
\v 41 The sonnes of Anah: \x + \xo 1:41 \xt Chap. 2.31.\x*Dishon. And the sonnes of Dishon: \x + \xo 1:41 \xt Or Hemdan, Gen. 36.26.\x*Amram, and Eshban, and Ithran, and Cheran.
\v 42 The sonnes of Ezer: Bilham, and Zauan, \add and\add* \x + \xo 1:42 \xt Or, Akan, Gen. 36.27.\x*Iakan. The sonnes of Dishon: Uz, and Aran.
\v 43 ¶ Now these \add are\add* the \x + \xo 1:43 \xt Gen. 36.31.\x*kings that reigned in the land of Edom, before \add any\add* king reigned ouer the children of Israel. Bela the sonne of Beor; and the name of his citie, \add was\add* Dinhabah.
\v 44 And when Bela was dead, Iobab the sonne of Zerah of Bosrah, reigned in his stead.
\v 45 And when Iobab was dead, Husham of the land of the Temanits, reigned in his stead.
\v 46 And when Husham was dead, Hadad, the sonne of Bedad (which smote Midian in the field of Moab) reigned in his stead: and the name of his citie \add was\add* Auith.
\v 47 And when Hadad was dead, Samlah of Masrekah, reigned in his stead.
\v 48 And when Samlah was dead, Shaul of Rehoboth \x + \xo 1:48 \xt Gen. 36.37.\x*by the riuer, reigned in his stead.
\v 49 And when Shaul was dead, Baal-hanan the sonne of Achbor, reigned in his stead.
\v 50 And when Baal-hanan was dead, \x + \xo 1:50 \xt Or, Hadar, Gen. 36.39\x*Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name of his citie \add was\add* \x + \xo 1:50 \xt Or, Pau, Gen. 36.39\x*Pai: and his wiues name \add was\add* Mehetabel the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.
\v 51 ¶ Hadad dyed also. And the \x + \xo 1:51 \xt Gen. 36.40.\x*Dukes of Edom were: Duke Timnah, Duke Aliah, Duke Ietheth,
\v 52 Duke Aholibamah, Duke Elah, Duke Pinon,
\v 53 Duke Kenaz, Duke Teman, Duke Mibzar,
\v 54 Duke Magdiel, Duke Iram. These \add are\add* the Dukes of Edom.
\c 2
\iex 1 The sonnes of Israel. 3 The posteritie of Iudah by Tamar. 13 The children of Iesse. 18 The posteritie of Caleb the sonne of Hesron. 21 Hesrons posteritie by the daughter of Machir. 25 Ierahmeels posteritie. 34 Sheshans posteritie. 42 another branch of Calebs posteritie. 50 The posteritie of Caleb the sonne of Hur.
\v 1 ¶ These \add are\add* the sonnes of \f + \fr 2:1 \ft Or, Iacob.\f*Israel: \x + \xo 2:1 \xt Gen. 29.32. & 30.5. & 35.18,22. & 46.8. &c.\x*Reuben, Simeon, Leui, and Iudah, Issachar, and Zebulun,
\v 2 Dan, Ioseph, and Beniamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.
\v 3 ¶ The sonnes of \x + \xo 2:3 \xt Gen.38.3. & 46.12.\x*Iudah: Er, and Onan, and Shelah. Which three were borne vnto him, of the daughter of Shua \x + \xo 2:3 \xt Gen. 38.2.\x*the Canaanites. And Er the first-borne of Iudah, was euill in the sight of the \nd LORD\nd*, and he slue him.
\v 4 And \x + \xo 2:4 \xt Gen. 38.29,30. Mat. 1.3.\x*Tamar his daughter-in law bare him Pharez, and Zerah. All the sonnes of Iudah \add were\add* fiue.
\v 5 The sonnes of \x + \xo 2:5 \xt Ruth. 4.18.\x*Pharez: Hezron, and Hamul.
\v 6 And the sonnes of Zerah: \x + \xo 2:6 \xt Or, Zabdi, Iosh. 7.1.\x*Zimri, \x + \xo 2:6 \xt 1.Kin. 4.31.\x*and Ethan, and Heman, and Calcol, and \f + \fr 2:6 \ft Or, Darda.\f*Dara. Fiue of them in all.
\v 7 And the sonnes of Carmi: \f + \fr 2:7 \ft Or, Achan.\f*Achar, the troubler of Israel, who transgressed in the thing \x + \xo 2:7 \xt Iosh. 6.19. and 7.1,25.\x*accursed.
\v 8 And the sonnes of Ethan: Azariah.
\v 9 The sonnes also of Hezron, that were borne vnto him: Ierahmeel, and \x + \xo 2:9 \xt Or, Aram. Mat. 1.3.\x*Ram, and \f + \fr 2:9 \ft Or, Caleb. \xt ver. 18.\f*Chelubai.
\v 10 And Ram \x + \xo 2:10 \xt Ruth. 4.19.\x*begate Aminadab, and Aminadab begat Nahshon, prince of the children of Iudah.
\v 11 And Nahshon begate Salma, and Salma begate Boaz.
\v 12 And Boaz begate Obed, and Obed begate Iesse.
\v 13 ¶ \x + \xo 2:13 \xt 1.Sam. 16.6.\x*And Iesse begate his first-borne Eliab, and Abinadab the second, and \x + \xo 2:13 \xt Or, Shamma, 1.Sam. 16.9.\x*Shimma the third,
\v 14 Nathanael the fourth, Raddai the fifth,
\v 15 Ozem the sixth, Dauid the seuenth:
\v 16 Whose sisters \add were\add* Zeruiah, and Abigail. And the sonnes of Zeruiah: Abishai, and Ioab, and Asahel, three.
\v 17 And Abigail bare Amasa. And the father of Amasa, \add was\add* Iether the Ishmeelite.
\v 18 ¶ And Caleb the sonne of Hezron, begate \add children\add* of Azubah \add his\add* wife, and of Ierioth: her sonnes \add are\add* these: Iesher, Shobab, and Ardon.
\v 19 And when Azubah was dead, Caleb tooke vnto him Ephrath, which bare him Hur.
\v 20 And Hur begate Uri, and Uri begate \x + \xo 2:20 \xt Exod. 31.2.\x*Bezaleel.
\v 21 ¶ And afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir, the father of Gilead, whom hee \f + \fr 2:21 \ft Heb. tooke.\f*married when he \add was\add* threescore yeeres old, and she bare him Segub.
\v 22 And Segub begate Iair, who had three and twenty cities in the land of Gilead.
\v 23 \x + \xo 2:23 \xt Num. 32.41. deut. 3.14. iosh. 13.30.\x*And he tooke Geshur, and Aram, with the townes of Iair, from them, with Kenath, and the townes thereof, \add euen\add* threescore cities. All these \add belonged to\add* the sonnes of Machir, the father of Gilead.
\v 24 And after that Hezron was dead in Caleb Ephratah, then Abiah Hezrons wife, bare him Ashur, the father of Tekoa.
\v 25 ¶ And the sonnes of Ierahmeel the first-borne of Hezron, were Ram the first-borne, and Bunah, and Oren, and Ozen, \add and\add* Ahiiah.
\v 26 Ierahmeel had also an other wife, whose name \add was\add* Atarah, she \add was\add* the mother of Onam.
\v 27 And the sonnes of Ram the first-borne of Ierahmeel, were Maaz, and Iamin, and Ekar.
\v 28 And the sonnes of Onam were, Shammai, and Iada. And the sonnes of Shammai: Nadab, and Abishur.
\v 29 And the name of the wife of Abishur \add was\add* Abihail, and shee bare him Ahban, and Molid.
\v 30 And the sonnes of Nadab: Seled, and Appaim. But Seled died without children.
\v 31 And the sonnes of Appaim, Ishi: and the sonnes of Ishi, Sheshan: and the children of Sheshan, Ahlai.
\v 32 And the sonnes of Iada the brother of Shammai, Iether, and Ionathan: and Iether died without children.
\v 33 And the sonnes of Ionathan, Peleth, and Zaza. These were the sonnes of Ierahmeel.
\v 34 ¶ Now Sheshan had no sonnes, but daughters: and Sheshan had a seruant, an Egyptian, whose name \add was\add* Iarha.
\v 35 And Sheshan gaue his daughter to Iarha his seruant to wife, and she bare him Attai.
\v 36 And Attai begate Nathan, and Nathan begate \x + \xo 2:36 \xt Chap. 11.41.\x*Zabad,
\v 37 And Zabad begate Ephlal, and Ephlal begate Obed,
\v 38 And Obed begate Iehu, and Iehu begate Azariah,
\v 39 And Azariah begate Helez, and Helez begate Eleasah,
\v 40 And Eleasah begate Sisamai, and Sisamai begate Shallum,
\v 41 And Shallum begate Iekamiah, and Iekamiah begate Elishama.
\v 42 ¶ Now the sonnes of Caleb the brother of Ierahmeel \add were\add*, Mesha his first-borne, which was the father of Ziph: and the sonnes of Maresha the father of Hebron.
\v 43 And the sonnes of Hebron: Korah, and Tappuah, and Rekem, and Shema.
\v 44 And Shema begat Raham, the father of Iorkoam: and Rekem begate Shammai.
\v 45 And the sonne of Shammai \add was\add* Maon: and Maon \add was\add* the father of Beth-zur.
\v 46 And Ephah Calebs concubine bare Haran, and Moza, and Gazez: and Haran begate Gazez.
\v 47 And the sonnes of Iahdai: Regem, and Iotham, and Geshan, and Pelet, and Ephah, and Shaaph.
\v 48 Maacha Calebs concubine, bare Sheber, and Tirhanah.
\v 49 Shee bare also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheua the father of Machbenah, & the father of Gibea: And the daughter of Caleb \x + \xo 2:49 \xt Iosh. 15.17.\x*\add was\add* Achsah.
\v 50 ¶ These were the sonnes of Caleb, the sonne of Hur, the first borne of Ephratah: Shobal the father of Kiriath-iearim,
\v 51 Salma the father of Bethlehem: Hareph the father of Beth-gader.
\v 52 And Shobal the father of Kiriath-iearim, had sonnes, \f + \fr 2:52 \ft Or, Reaiah, \xt chap. 4.2.\f*Haroe, \add and\add* \f + \fr 2:52 \ft Or, halfe of the Menuchites, Or Hatsi-hammenuchoth.\f*halfe of the Manahethites.
\v 53 And the families of Kiriath-iearim, the Ithrites, and the Puhites, and the Shumathites, and the Mishraites: of them came the Zareathites, and the Eshtaulites.
\v 54 The sonnes of Salmah: Bethlehem, and the Netophathites, \f + \fr 2:54 \ft Or, Atarites, or, crownes of the house of Ioab.\f*Ataroth, the house of Ioab, and halfe of the Manahethites, the Zorites.
\v 55 And the families of the Scribes, which dwelt at Iabez: the Tirathites, the Shimeathites, \add and\add* Suchathites. These \add are\add* the \x + \xo 2:55 \xt Iud. 1.16.\x*Kenites that came of Hemath, the father of the house of \x + \xo 2:55 \xt Ier. 35.2.\x*Rechab.
\c 3
\iex 1 The sonnes of Dauid. 10 His line to Zedekiah. 17 The successors of Ieconiah.
\v 1 ¶ Now these were the sonnes of Dauid, which were borne vnto him in Hebron. The first borne \x + \xo 3:1 \xt 2.Sam. 3.2.\x*Amnon, of Ahinoam the \x + \xo 3:1 \xt Iosh. 15.56.\x*Iesreelitesse: the second \f + \fr 3:1 \ft Or, Chileab, \xt 2.sam. 3.3.\f*Daniel, of Abigail the Carmelitesse:
\v 2 The third, Absalom the sonne of Maacha, the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur: the fourth, Adoniah the sonne of Haggith:
\v 3 The fifth, Shephatia of Abital: the sixth, Ithream by \x + \xo 3:3 \xt 2.Sam. 3.5.\x*Eglah his wife.
\v 4 \add These\add* sixe were borne vnto him in Hebron, and there hee reigned seuen yeeres, and sixe moneths: and in Ierusalem he reigned thirty and three yeres.
\v 5 \x + \xo 3:5 \xt 2.Sam. 5.14.\x*And these were borne vnto him in Ierusalem. \f + \fr 3:5 \ft Or, Shammua, \xt 2.Sam. 5.14.\f*Shimea, and Shobab, and Nathan, and Solomon, foure, of \f + \fr 3:5 \ft Or, Bethsabe, \xt 2.Sam. 11.13.\f*Bathshua the daughter of \f + \fr 3:5 \ft Or, Eliam, \xt 2.Sam.11.3.\f*Ammiel.
\v 6 Ibhar also, and \f + \fr 3:6 \ft Or, Elishua \xt 2.Sam. 5.15.\f*Elishama, and Eliphelet,
\v 7 And Noga, and Nepheg, and Iaphia,
\v 8 And Elishama, and \f + \fr 3:8 \ft Or, Beliada, \xt 1.Chro. 14.7.\f*Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine.
\v 9 \add These were\add* all the sonnes of Dauid: beside the sonnes of the concubines, and Tamar \x + \xo 3:9 \xt 2.Sam. 13.1.\x*their sister.
\v 10 ¶ And Solomons sonne \add was\add* \x + \xo 3:10 \xt 1.King. 11.43. & 15.8.\x*Rehoboam: \f + \fr 3:10 \ft Or, Abiam, \xt 1.king. 15.1.\f*Abia his sonne: Asa his son: Iehoshaphat his sonne:
\v 11 Ioram his sonne: \f + \fr 3:11 \ft Or, Azariah, \xt 2.Chr. 22.6. & 21.17.\f*Ahaziah his sonne: Ioash his sonne:
\v 12 Amaziah his sonne: \f + \fr 3:12 \ft Or, Vzziah \xt 2.king. 15.30.\f*Azariah his sonne: Iotham his sonne:
\v 13 Ahaz his sonne: Hezekiah his sonne: Manasseh his sonne:
\v 14 Amon his sonne: Iosiah his sonne.
\v 15 And the sonnes of Iosiah \add were\add*: the first borne \f + \fr 3:15 \ft Or, Ioachaz, \xt 2.king. 23.30.\f*Iohanan, the second \f + \fr 3:15 \ft Or, Eliakim, \xt 2.king. 23.34.\f*Ioakim, the third \f + \fr 3:15 \ft Or, Mathania, \xt 2.kin. 24.17.\f*Zedekiah, the fourth Sallum.
\v 16 And the sonnes of \x + \xo 3:16 \xt Mat. 1.11.\x*Ioakim: \f + \fr 3:16 \ft Or, Iehoiachin, \xt 2.King. 24.6.\f*Ieconiah his sonne, \f + \fr 3:16 \ft Or, Coniah, \xt ier. 22.24.\f*Zedekiah his sonne.
\v 17 ¶ And the sonnes of \f + \fr 3:17 \ft Or, Iehoiachin, \xt 2.King. 24.6.\f*Ieconiah, Assir, \f + \fr 3:17 \ft Heb. Shealtiel.\f*Salathiel \x + \xo 3:17 \xt 2.King. 24.17. being his vncle.\x*\x + \xo 3:17 \xt Mat.1.12.\x*his sonne,
\v 18 Malchiram also, and Pedaiah, and Shenazar, Iecamiah, Hosama, and Nedabiah.
\v 19 And the sonnes of Pedaiah \add were\add*: Zerubbabel, and Shimei: And the sonne of Zerubbabel, Meshullam, and Hananiah, and Shelomith their sister.
\v 20 And Hazubah, and Ohel, and Berechiah, & Hasadiah, Iushabhesed, fiue.
\v 21 And the sonnes of Hananiah, Pelatiah, and Iesaiah: the sonnes of Rephaiah, the sons of Arnan, the sonnes of Obadiah, the sonnes of Sechaniah.
\v 22 And the sonnes of Sechaniah, Semaiah: and the sonnes of Semaiah, Hattush, and Igeal, and Bariah, and Neariah, and Shaphat, sixe.
\v 23 And the sonnes of Neariah: Elioenai, and \f + \fr 3:23 \ft Heb. Hiskijah.\f*Hezekiah, and Azrikam, three.
\v 24 And the sonnes of Elioenai, \add were\add*: Hodaiah, and Eliashib, and Pelaiah, and Akkub, and Iohanan, and Dalaiah, and Anani, seuen.
\c 4
\iex 1.11 The posteritie of Iudah by Caleb the sonne of Hur. 5 Of Ashur the posthumus son of Hezron. 9 Of Iabez, and his prayer. 21 The posteritie of Shelah. 24 The posteritie and cities of Simeon. 39 Their conquest of Gedor, and of the Amalekites in mount Seir.
\v 1 ¶ The sonnes of Iudah: \x + \xo 4:1 \xt Gen. 38.29. and 46.12.\x*Pharez, Hezron, and \f + \fr 4:1 \ft Or, Chelubai, \xt Chap. 2.9.\ft or Caleb, \xt Chap. 2.18.\f*Carmi, and Hur, and Shobal.
\v 2 And \x + \xo 4:2 \xt Or, Haroe, Chap. 2.52.\x*Reaiah, the son of Shobal, begate Iahath, and Iahath begate Ahumai, & Lahad. These \add are\add* the families of the Zorathites.
\v 3 And these \add were of\add* the father of Etam: Iezreel & Ishma, & Idbash: and the name of their sister \add was\add* Hazelelponi.
\v 4 And Penuel the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah. These \add are\add* the sonnes of Hur, the first borne of Ephratah, the father of Bethlehem.
\v 5 ¶ And \x + \xo 4:5 \xt Cha. 2.24.\x*Ashur the father of Tekoa, had two wiues: Helah, & Naarah.
\v 6 And Naarah bare him Ahusam, and Hepher, and Temeni, and Ahashtari. These \add were\add* the sonnes of Naarah.
\v 7 And the sonnes of Helah \add were\add*: Zereth, and Zoar, and Ethnan.
\v 8 And Coz begate Anub, and Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel, the sonne of Harum.
\v 9 ¶ And Iabez was more honourable then his brethren: and his mother called his name \f + \fr 4:9 \ft That is, sorrowfull.\f*Iabez, saying, Because I bare him with sorrow.
\v 10 And Iabez called on the God of Israel, saying, \f + \fr 4:10 \ft Heb. If thou wilt, &c.\f*Oh that thou wouldest blesse mee indeede, and enlarge my coast, and that thine hand might bee with me, and that thou wouldest \f + \fr 4:10 \ft Heb. doe me.\f*keepe mee from euill, that it may not grieue \add me\add*. And God granted him that which he requested.
\v 11 ¶ And Chelub the brother of Shuah, begate Mehir, which \add was\add* the father of Eshton.
\v 12 And Eshton begate Beth-rapha, and Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of \f + \fr 4:12 \ft Or, the city of Nahash.\f*Ir-nahash. These \add are\add* the men of Rechah.
\v 13 And the sonnes of Kenaz: Othniel, and Saraia: and the sonnes of Othniel, \f + \fr 4:13 \ft Or, Hathath, and Meonothai, who begate, &c.\f*Hathath.
\v 14 And Meonothai begate Ophrah: and Seraiah begate Ioab, the father of the \f + \fr 4:14 \ft Or, inhabitants of the valley.\f*valley of \f + \fr 4:14 \ft That is, craftesmen.\f*Charasim, for they were craftesmen.
\v 15 And the sonnes of Caleb the sonne of Iephunneh: Iru, Elah, and Naam, and the sonnes of Elah, \f + \fr 4:15 \ft Or, Vknaz.\f*euen Kenaz.
\v 16 And the sonnes of Iehaleleel: Ziph, and Ziphah, Tiria, and Asareel.
\v 17 And the sonnes of Ezra \add were\add*: Iether, and Mered, and Epher, and Ialon: and she bare Miriam, and Shammai, & Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa.
\v 18 And his wife \f + \fr 4:18 \ft Or, the Iewesse.\f*Iehudiiah bare Iered the father of Gedor, and Heber the father of Socho, and Iekuthiel the father of Zanoah. And these \add are\add* the sonnes of Bithiah the daughter of Pharaoh, which Mered tooke.
\v 19 And the sonnes of \add his\add* wife \f + \fr 4:19 \ft Or, Iehudiiah, mentioned before.\f*Hodiah, the sister of Naham the father of Keilah, the Garmite, and Eshtemoa the Maachathite.
