\v 26 For all the gods \x + \xo 16:26 \xt Leu. 19.4.\x*of the people \add are\add* idoles: but the \nd LORD\nd* made the heauens.
\v 27 Glory and honour \add are\add* in his presence: strength and gladnesse \add are\add* in his place.
\v 28 Giue vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, yee kinreds of the people: giue vnto the \nd LORD\nd* glory and strength.
\v 29 Giue vnto the \nd LORD\nd* the glory \add due\add* vnto his Name: bring an offering, and come before him, worship the \nd LORD\nd* in the beautie of holinesse.
\v 30 Feare before him all the earth: the world also shall be stable, that it be not mooued.
\v 31 Let the heauens be glad, and let the earth reioyce: and let \add men\add* say among the nations, The \nd LORD\nd* reigneth.
\v 32 Let the sea roare, and the fulnesse thereof: let the fieldes reioyce, and all that \add is\add* therein.
\v 33 Then shall the trees of the wood sing out at the presence of the \nd LORD\nd*, because hee commeth to iudge the earth.
\v 34 \x + \xo 16:34 \xt Psa. 107.1 and 118.1. and 136.1.\x*O giue thanks vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, for hee is good: for his mercy \add endureth\add* for euer.
\v 35 And say yee, Saue vs, O God of our saluation, and gather vs together, and deliuer vs from the heathen, that we may giue thanks to thy holy Name, \add and\add* glory in thy praise.
\v 36 Blessed \add be\add* the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel for euer and euer: and all \x + \xo 16:36 \xt Deut. 27.15.\x*the people saide, Amen, and praised the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 37 ¶ So hee left there before the Arke of the couenant of the \nd LORD\nd*, Asaph and his brethren, to minister before the Arke continually, as euery dayes worke required:
\v 38 And Obed Edom with their brethren, threescore and eight: Obed Edom also the sonne of Ieduthun, and Hosah \add to be\add* porters:
\v 39 And Zadok the Priest, and his brethren the Priests, before the Tabernacle of the \nd LORD\nd*, in the high place that \add was\add* at Gibeon,
\v 40 To offer burnt offerings vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, vpon the Altar of the burnt offering continually \f + \fr 16:40 \ft Heb. in the morning and in the euening.\f*morning and euening, and to doe according to all that is written in the Lawe of the \nd LORD\nd*, which hee commanded Israel:
\v 41 And with them Heman and Ieduthun, and the rest that were chosen, who were expressed by name, to giue thankes to the \nd LORD\nd*, because his mercy \add endureth\add* for euer.
\v 42 And with them Heman and Ieduthun with trumpets and cymbales, for those that should make a sound, and with musicall instruments of God: and the sonnes of Ieduthun \add were\add* \f + \fr 16:42 \ft Heb. for the gate.\f*Porters.
\v 43 And all the people departed euery man to his house, and Dauid returned to blesse his house.
\c 17
\iex 1 Nathan first approouing the purpose of Dauid, to build God an house, 3 after by the word of God forbiddeth him. 11 Hee promiseth him blessings and benefits in his seed. 16 Dauids prayer and thankesgiuing.
\v 1 ¶ Now \x + \xo 17:1 \xt 2.Sam. 7.1, &c.\x*it came to passe, as Dauid sate in his house, that Dauid sayde to Nathan the Prophet, Loe, I dwell in an house of Cedars, but the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd* \add remaineth\add* vnder curtaines.
\v 2 Then Nathan sayd vnto Dauid, Doe all that \add is\add* in thine heart, for God \add is\add* with thee.
\v 3 ¶ And it came to passe the same night, that the word of God came to Nathan, saying,
\v 4 Goe and tell Dauid my seruant, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*, Thou shalt not build me an house to dwell in.
\v 5 For I haue not dwelt in a house since the day that I brought vp Israel, vnto this day, but \f + \fr 17:5 \ft Heb. haue bene.\f*haue gone from tent to tent, and from \add one\add* Tabernacle \add to another\add*.
\v 6 Wheresoeuer I haue walked with all Israel, spake I a word to any of the Iudges of Israel (whom I commanded to feed my people) saying, Why haue ye not built me an house of Cedars?
\v 7 Now therefore thus shalt thou say vnto my seruant Dauid, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd* of hosts, I tooke thee from the Sheep-coat, \add euen\add* \f + \fr 17:7 \ft Heb. from after.\f*from folowing the sheep, that thou shouldest be ruler ouer my people Israel:
\v 8 And I haue bene with thee whithersoeuer thou hast walked, and haue cut off all thine enemies from before thee, and haue made thee a name, like the name of the great men that \add are\add* in the earth.
\v 9 Also I will ordeine a place for my people Israel, and will plant them, and they shall dwell in their place, and shall be moued no more: neither shal the children of wickednesse waste them any more (as at the beginning,
\v 10 And since the time that I commanded Iudges \add to bee\add* ouer my people Israel.) Moreouer, I will subdue all thine enemies. Furthermore I tel thee, that the \nd LORD\nd* will build thee an house.
\v 11 ¶ And it shall come to passe, when thy dayes be expired, that thou must go \add to be\add* with thy fathers, that I will raise vp thy seed after thee, which shall bee of thy sonnes, and I wil stablish his kingdome.
\v 12 He shall build me an house, and I will stablish his throne for euer.
\v 13 I \x + \xo 17:13 \xt 2.King. 9.14.\x*will be his father, and he shall be my sonne, and I will not take my mercie away from him, as I tooke \add it\add* from \add him\add* that was before thee.
\v 14 But I will settle him in mine house, and in my kingdom for euer, and his throne shall bee established for euermore.
\v 15 According to all these words, and according to all this vision, so did Nathan speake vnto Dauid.
\v 16 ¶ And Dauid the king came, and sate before the \nd LORD\nd*, and said, Who \add am\add* I, O \nd LORD\nd* God, and what \add is\add* mine house, that thou hast brought mee hitherto?
\v 17 And \add yet\add* this was a small thing in thine eyes, O God: for thou hast \add also\add* spoken of thy seruants house, for a great while to come, and hast regarded mee according to the estate of a man of high degree, O \nd LORD\nd* God.
\v 18 What can Dauid speake more to thee for the honour of thy seruant? for thou knowest thy seruant.
\v 19 O \nd LORD\nd*, for thy seruants sake, and according to thine owne heart, hast thou done all this greatnesse in making knowen all \add these\add* \f + \fr 17:19 \ft Heb. greatnesses.\f*great things.
\v 20 O \nd LORD\nd*, \add there is\add* none like thee neither \add is there any\add* God besides thee, according to all that we haue heard with our eares.
\v 21 And what one nation in the earth \add is\add* like thy people Israel, whome God went to redeeme \add to be\add* his owne people, to make thee a name of greatnesse and terriblenesse, by driuing out nations from before thy people whom thou hast redeemed out of Egypt?
\v 22 For thy people Israel didst thou make thine owne people for euer, and thou, \nd LORD\nd*, becamest their God.
\v 23 Therefore now \nd LORD\nd*, let the thing that thou hast spoken concerning thy seruant, and concerning his house, be established for euer, and doe as thou hast said.
\v 24 Let it euen bee established, that thy name may bee magnified for euer, saying, The \nd LORD\nd* of hosts \add is\add* the God of Israel, \add euen\add* a God to Israel: and \add let\add* the house of Dauid thy seruant \add be\add* established before thee.
\v 25 For thou, O my God, \f + \fr 17:25 \ft Heb. hast reuealed the eare of thy seruant.\f*hast tolde thy seruant that thou wilt build him an house: therefore thy seruant hath found \add in his heart\add* to pray before thee.
\v 26 And now, \nd LORD\nd* (thou art God, and hast promised this goodnesse vnto thy seruant.)
\v 27 Now therefore \f + \fr 17:27 \ft Or, it hath pleased thee.\f*let it please thee to blesse the house of thy seruant, that it may bee before thee for euer: for thou blessest, O \nd LORD\nd*, and it shalbe blessed for euer.
\c 18
\iex 1 Dauid subdueth the Philistines and the Moabites. 3 He smiteth Hadadezer and the Syrians. 9 Tou sendeth Hadoram with presents to blesse Dauid. 11 The presents & the spoile, Dauid dedicateth to God. 13 He putteth garisons in Edom. 14 Dauids officers.
\v 1 ¶ Now after this, \x + \xo 18:1 \xt 2.Sam. 8.1. &c.\x*it came to passe, that Dauid smote the Philistines & subdued them, and tooke Gath, and her townes out of the hand of the Philistines.
\v 2 And he smote Moab, and the Moabites became Dauids seruants, \add and\add* brought gifts.
\v 3 ¶ And Dauid smote \f + \fr 18:3 \ft Or. Hadadezer in Sam.\f*Hadarezer king of Zobah vnto Hamath, as hee went to stablish his dominion by the riuer Euphrates.
\v 4 And Dauid tooke from him a thousand charets, and seuen thousand horsemen, and twentie thousand footmen: Dauid also houghed all the charet \add horses\add*, but reserued of them an hundred charets.
\v 5 And when the Syrians of \f + \fr 18:5 \ft Heb. Darmesek.\f*Damascus came to helpe Hadarezer king of Zobah, Dauid slew of the Syrians two and twentie thousand men.
\v 6 Then Dauid put garisons in Syria Damascus, \add and\add* the Syrians became Dauids seruants, and brought giftes. Thus the \nd LORD\nd* preserued Dauid, whithersoeuer he went.
\v 7 And Dauid tooke the shields of golde that were on the seruants of Hadarezer, & brought them to Ierusalem.
\v 8 Likewise from \f + \fr 18:8 \ft Called in the booke of Sam. Beta and Berothai.\f*Tibhath, and from Chun, cities of Hadarezer, broght Dauid very much brasse, wherewith \x + \xo 18:8 \xt 1.King. 7.23. and 2.Chro. 4.15.\x*Solomon made the brasen Sea, and the pillars, and the vessels of brasse.
\v 9 ¶ Now when \f + \fr 18:9 \ft Or, Toi, \xt 2.Sam. 8.9.\f*Tou king of Hamath heard how Dauid had smitten all the hoste of Hadarezer king of Zobah:
\v 10 Hee sent \f + \fr 18:10 \ft Or, Ioram, \xt 2.Sam. 8.10.\f*Hadoram his sonne to king Dauid, \f + \fr 18:10 \ft Or, to salute.\f*to enquire of his welfare, and to \f + \fr 18:10 \ft Heb. to blesse.\f*congratulate him, because hee had fought against Hadarezer, and smitten him (for Hadarezer \f + \fr 18:10 \ft Heb. was the man of warres.\f*had warre with Tou) and \add with him\add* all manner of vessels of golde and siluer, and brasse.
\v 11 ¶ Them also king Dauid dedicated vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, with the siluer and the golde that he brought from all \add these\add* nations: from Edom, and from Moab, and from the children of Ammon, and from the Philistines, and from Amalek.
\v 12 Moreouer, Abishai the sonne of Zeruiah, slew of the Edomites in the valley of salt, eighteene thousand.
\v 13 ¶ And he put garisons in Edom, and all the Edomites became Dauids seruants. Thus the \nd LORD\nd* preserued Dauid whithersoeuer he went.
\v 14 ¶ So Dauid reigned ouer all Israel, and executed iudgement and iustice among all his people.
\v 15 And Ioab the sonne of Zeruiah \add was\add* ouer the hoste, and Iehoshaphat the sonne of Ahilud, \f + \fr 18:15 \ft Or, Remembrancer.\f*Recorder.
\v 16 And Zadok the sonne of Ahitub, and \f + \fr 18:16 \ft Called Ahimelech in Sam.\f*Abimelech the sonne of Abiathar, \add were\add* the Priests, and \f + \fr 18:16 \ft Called Saraia in Sam. and Sisa, \xt 1.King. 4.2.\f*Shausha was Scribe.
\v 17 And Benaiah the sonne of Iehoiada \add was\add* ouer the Cherethites, and the Pelethites: and the sonnes of Dauid \add were\add* \f + \fr 18:17 \ft Heb. at the hand of the King.\f*chiefe about the king.
\c 19
\iex 1 Dauids messengers sent to comfort Hanun the sonne of Nahash, are villanously intreated. 6 The Ammonites strengthened by the Syrians, are ouercome by Ioab and Abishai. 16 Shophach making a new supply of the Syrians, is slaine by Dauid.
\v 1 ¶ Now \x + \xo 19:1 \xt 2.Sam. 10.1, &c.\x*it came to passe after this, that Nahash the King of the children of Ammon dyed, & his sonne reigned in his stead.
\v 2 And Dauid sayde, I will shewe kindnesse vnto Hanun the sonne of Nahash, because his father shewed kindnesse to mee. And Dauid sent messengers to comfort him concerning his father. So the seruants of Dauid came into the land of the children of Ammon, to Hanun, to comfort him.
\v 3 But the Princes of the children of Ammon sayde to Hanun, \f + \fr 19:3 \ft Heb. In thine eyes doeth Dauid, &c.\f*Thinkest thou that Dauid doeth honour thy father, that he hath sent comforters vnto thee? Are not his seruants come vnto thee for to search, and to ouerthrow, and to spie out the land?
\v 4 Wherefore Hanun tooke Dauids seruants, and shaued them, and cut off their garments in the middest, hard by their buttockes, and sent them away.
\v 5 Then there went certeine, and told Dauid, how the men were serued, and hee sent to meet them (for the men were greatly ashamed) and the King sayde, Tary at Iericho vntill your beards be growen, and \add then\add* returne.
\v 6 ¶ And when the children of Ammon sawe, that they had made themselues \f + \fr 19:6 \ft Heb. to stinke.\f*odious to Dauid; Hanun and the children of Ammon sent a thousand talents of siluer, to hire them charets and horsemen out of Mesopotamia, and out of Syria-Maachah, and out of Zobah.
\v 7 So they hired thirtie and two thousand charets, and the king of Maachah and his people, who came and pitched before Medeba. And the children of Ammon gathered themselues together from their cities, and came to battaile.
\v 8 And when Dauid heard \add of it\add*, hee sent Ioab, and all the host of the mightie men.
\v 9 And the children of Ammon came out, and put the battell in aray before the gate of the citie, and the kings that were come, \add were\add* by themselues in the field.
\v 10 Now when Ioab saw that \f + \fr 19:10 \ft Hebr. the face of the battell was.\f*the battell was set against him, before and behinde: hee chose out of all the \f + \fr 19:10 \ft Or, yong men.\f*choice of Israel, and put \add them\add* in aray against the Syrians.
\v 11 And the rest of the people hee deliuered vnto the hand of \f + \fr 19:11 \ft Hebr Abshai.\f*Abishai his brother, and they set \add themselues\add* in aray against the children of Ammon.
\v 12 And he said, If the Syrians bee too strong for me, then thou shalt helpe me: but if the children of Ammon be too strong for thee, then I wil helpe thee.
\v 13 Be of good courage, and let vs behaue our selues valiantly for our people, and for the Cities of our God: and let the \nd LORD\nd* do \add that which is\add* good in his sight.
\v 14 So Ioab and the people that \add were\add* with him, drew nigh before the Syrians, vnto the battell; and they fled before him.
\v 15 And when the children of Ammon saw that the Syrians were fled, they likewise fled before Abishai his brother, and entred into the city. Then Ioab came to Ierusalem.
\v 16 ¶ And when the Syrians saw that they were put to the worse before Israel, they sent messengers, and drew forth the Syrians, that \add were\add* beyond the \f + \fr 19:16 \ft i.Euphrates.\f*Riuer: and \f + \fr 19:16 \ft Or Shobach, \xt 2.sam. 10.16.\f*Shophach the captaine of the hoste of Hadarezer, \add went\add* before them.
\v 17 And it was tolde Dauid, and hee gathered all Israel, and passed ouer Iordane, and came vpon them, and set the battell in aray against them: so when Dauid had put the battell in aray against the Syrians, they fought with him.
\v 18 But the Syrians fled before Israel, and Dauid slew of the Syrians seuen thousand men, which fought in charets, and fourty thousand footmen, and killed Shophach the captaine of the hoste.
\v 19 And when the seruants of Hadarezer saw that they were put to the worse before Israel, they made peace with Dauid, and became his seruants: neither would the Syrians helpe the children of Ammon any more.
\c 20
\iex 1 Rabbah is besieged by Ioab, spoiled by Dauid, and the people thereof tortured. 4 Three giants are slaine in three seuerall ouerthrowes of the Philistines.
\v 1 ¶ And \x + \xo 20:1 \xt 2.Sam. 11.1.\x*it came to passe, that \f + \fr 20:1 \ft Hebr. at the returne of the yeere.\f*after the yeere was expired, at the time that kings goe out to battell, Ioab led forth the power of the armie, and wasted the countrey of the children of Ammon, and came and besieged Rabbah (but Dauid taried at Ierusalem,) and Ioab smote Rabbah, and destroyed it.
\v 2 And Dauid \x + \xo 20:2 \xt 2.Sam. 12.26.\x*tooke the crowne of their king from off his head, and found it \f + \fr 20:2 \ft Hebr. the weight of.\f*to weigh a talent of gold, and \add there were\add* precious stones in it, and it was set vpon Dauids head; and hee brought also exceeding much spoile out of the city.
\v 3 And hee brought out the people that \add were\add* in it, and cut \add them\add* with sawes, and with harrowes of yron, and with axes: euen so dealt Dauid with all the cities of the children of Ammon. And Dauid and all the people returned to Ierusalem.
\v 4 ¶ And it came to passe after this, \x + \xo 20:4 \xt 2.Sam. 21.18.\x*that there \f + \fr 20:4 \ft Or, continued, Hebr. stood.\f*arose warre at \f + \fr 20:4 \ft Or, Gob.\f*Gezer with the Philistines, at which time Sibbechai the Hushathite, slew Sippai, \add that was\add* of the children of \f + \fr 20:4 \ft Or, Rapha.\f*the giant: and they were subdued.
\v 5 And there was warre againe with the Philistines, and Elhanan the sonne of \f + \fr 20:5 \ft Called also Iaare-ore-gim, \xt 2.sam. 21.19.\f*Iair, slew Lahmi the brother of Goliath the Gittite, whose spearestaffe \add was\add* like a weauers beame.
\v 6 And yet againe \x + \xo 20:6 \xt 2.Sam. 21.20.\x*there was warre at Gath, where was a man \f + \fr 20:6 \ft Hebr. a man of measure.\f*of \add great\add* stature, whose fingers and toes \add were\add* foure and twentie, sixe \add on each hand\add*, and sixe \add on each foot\add*. And he also was \f + \fr 20:6 \ft Hebr. borne to the giant Or, Rapha.\f*the sonne of the giant.
\v 7 But when he \f + \fr 20:7 \ft Or, reproched.\f*defied Israel, Ionathan the sonne of \f + \fr 20:7 \ft Called Shammah, \xt 1.Sam. 16.9.\f*Shimea Dauids brother, slew him.
\v 8 These were borne vnto the Giant in Gath, and they fell by the hand of Dauid, and by the hand of his seruants.
\c 21
\iex 1 Dauid tempted by Satan, forceth Ioab to number the people. 5 The number of the people being brought, Dauid repenteth of it. 9 Dauid hauing three plagues propounded by Gad, chuseth the pestilence. 14 After the death of 70000, Dauid by repentance preuenteth the destruction of Ierusalem. 18 Dauid by Gads direction, purchaseth Ornans threshing floore, where hauing built an Altar, God giueth a signe of his fauour by fire, and stayeth the plague. 28 Dauid sacrificeth there, being restrained from Gibeon by feare of the Angel.
\v 1 ¶ And \x + \xo 21:1 \xt 2.Sam. 24.1, &c.\x*Satan stoode vp against Israel, and prouoked Dauid to number Israel.
\v 2 And Dauid saide to Ioab, and to the rulers of the people, Goe, number Israel from Beer-sheba eueu to Dan: and bring the number of them to me, that I may know \add it\add*.
\v 3 And Ioab answered, The \nd LORD\nd* make his people an hundred times so many moe as they \add bee\add*: but, my lord the king, \add are\add* they not al my lords seruants? why then doeth my lord require this thing? why will hee bee a cause of trespasse to Israel?
\v 4 Neuerthelesse, the kings word preuailed against Ioab: wherefore Ioab departed, and went throughout all Israel, and came to Ierusalem.
\v 5 ¶ And Ioab gaue the summe of the number of the people vnto Dauid: and all \add they of\add* Israel were a thousand thousand, and an hundred thousand men that drew sword: and Iudah \add was\add* foure hundred threescore and ten thousand men, that drew sword.
\v 6 But Leui and Beniamin counted hee not among them: for the kings word was abominable to Ioab.
\v 7 \f + \fr 21:7 \ft And it was euill in the eyes of the LORD concerning this thing.\f*And God was displeased with this thing, therefore he smote Israel.
\v 8 And Dauid saide vnto God, \x + \xo 21:8 \xt 2.Sam. 24.10.\x*I haue sinned greatly, because I haue done this thing: but uow, I beseech thee, doe away the iniquitie of thy seruant, for I haue done very foolishly.
\v 9 ¶ And the \nd LORD\nd* spake vnto Gad, Dauids Seer, saying,
\v 10 Goe and tell Dauid, saying, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*, I \f + \fr 21:10 \ft Hebr. stretch out.\f*offer thee three \add things\add*, choose thee one of them, that I may doe \add it\add* vnto thee.
\v 11 So Gad came to Dauid, and said vnto him, Thus saith the \nd LORD\nd*, \f + \fr 21:11 \ft Hebr. take to thee.\f*Choose thee
\v 12 Either three yeeres famine, or three moneths to bee destroyed before thy foes (while that the sword of thine enemies ouertaketh \add thee\add*) or else three dayes the sword of the \nd LORD\nd*, euen the pestilence in the land, and the Angel of the \nd LORD\nd* destroying throughout all the coasts of Israel. Now therefore aduise thy selfe, what word I shall bring againe to him that sent me.
\v 13 And Dauid said vnto Gad, I am in a great strait. Let mee fall now into the hand of the \nd LORD\nd* (for very \f + \fr 21:13 \ft Or, many.\f*great \add are\add* his mercies,) but let me not fall into the hand of man.
\v 14 ¶ So the \nd LORD\nd* sent pestilence vpon Israel: and there fell of Israel, seuentie thousand men.
\v 15 And God sent an \x + \xo 21:15 \xt 2.Sam. 24.16.\x*Angel vnto Ierusalem to destroy it: and as he was destroying, the \nd LORD\nd* beheld, and he repented him of the euill, and said to the Angel that destroyed, It is ynough, stay now thine hand. And the Angel of the \nd LORD\nd* stood by the threshing floore of \f + \fr 21:15 \ft Or, Araunah. \xt 2.sam. 24.18.\f*Ornan the Iebusite.
\v 16 And Dauid lift vp his eyes, and saw the Angel of the \nd LORD\nd* stand betweene the earth and the heauen, hauing a drawen sword in his hand stretched out ouer Ierusalem. Then Dauid and the Elders \add of Israel, who were\add* clothed in sackecloth, fell vpon their faces.
\v 17 And Dauid said vnto God, \add Is it\add* not I \add that\add* commanded the people to be numbred? euen I it is that haue sinned, and done euill indeed, but \add as for\add* these sheepe, what haue they done? Let thine hand, I pray thee, O \nd LORD\nd* my God, be on me, and on my fathers house, but not on thy people, that they should bee plagued.
\v 18 ¶ Then the \x + \xo 21:18 \xt 2.Chron. 3.1.\x*Angel of the \nd LORD\nd* commanded Gad to say to Dauid, that Dauid should goe vp and set vp an Altar vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, in the threshing floore of Ornan the Iebusite.
\v 19 And Dauid went vp at the saying of Gad, which he spake in the Name of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 20 \f + \fr 21:20 \ft Or, when Ornan turned backe, and saw the Angel, then he and his foure sonnes with him, hid themselues.\f*And Ornan turned backe and saw the Angel, and his foure sonnes with him, hid themselues. Now Ornan was threshing wheat.
\v 21 And as Dauid came to Ornan, Ornan looked and saw Dauid, and went out of the threshing floore, and bowed himselfe to Dauid with \add his\add* face to the ground.
\v 22 Then Dauid saide to Ornan, \f + \fr 21:22 \ft Heb. giue.\f*Grant mee the place of \add this\add* threshing floore, that I may build an Altar therein vnto the \nd LORD\nd*: thou shalt grant it mee for the full price, that the plague may be stayed from the people.
\v 23 And Ornan saide vnto Dauid, Take \add it\add* to thee, and let my lord the king do \add that which is\add* good in his eyes. Loe, I giue \add thee\add* the oxen \add also\add* for burnt offerings, and the threshing instruments for wood, and the wheat for the meate offering, I giue it all.
\v 24 And king Dauid said to Ornan; Nay, but I wil verily buy it for the full price: for I will not take \add that\add* which \add is\add* thine for the \nd LORD\nd*, nor offer burnt offerings without cost.
\v 25 So \x + \xo 21:25 \xt 2.Sam. 24.24.\x*Dauid gaue to Ornan for the place, sixe hundred shekels of gold by weight.
\v 26 And Dauid built there an Altar vnto the \nd LORD\nd*, and offered burnt offerings, and peace offerings, and called vpon the \nd LORD\nd*, and hee answered him from heauen by fire vpon the Altar of burnt offering.
\v 27 And the \nd LORD\nd* commaunded the Angel, and hee put vp his sword againe into the sheath thereof.
\v 28 ¶ At that time, when Dauid saw that the \nd LORD\nd* had answered him in the threshing floore of Ornan the Iebusite, then he sacrificed there.
\v 29 For the tabernacle of the \nd LORD\nd* which Moses made in the wildernesse, and the Altar of the burnt offering \add were\add* at that season, in the high place at \x + \xo 21:29 \xt Chap. 16.39. 2.Chro. 1.3. 1.king. 3.4.\x*Gibeon:
\v 30 But Dauid could not goe before it to euquire of God; for he was afraid, because of the sword of the Angel of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\c 22
\iex 1 Dauid foreknowing the place of the Temple, prepareth abundance for the building of it. 6 Hee instructeth Solomon in Gods promises, and his duety in building the Temple. 17 He chargeth the Princes to assist his sonne.
\v 1 ¶ Then Dauid said, This \add is\add* the house of the \nd LORD\nd* God, and this \add is\add* the Altar of the burnt offering for Israel.
\v 2 And Dauid commanded to gather together the strangers that \add were\add* in the land of Israel: and hee set masons to hew wrought stones to build the house of God.
\v 3 And Dauid prepared yron in abundance for the nailes for the doores of the gates, and for the ioynings, and brasse in abundance without weight;
\v 4 Also Cedar trees in abundance: for the Zidonians, and they of Tyre, brought much Cedar wood to Dauid.
\v 5 And Dauid said, \x + \xo 22:5 \xt Chap. 29.1.\x*Solomon my sonne \add is\add* yong and tender, and the house \add that is\add* to be builded for the \nd LORD\nd*, \add must be\add* exceeding magnificall, of fame and of glory throughout all countreys: I will \add therefore\add* now make preparation for it. So Dauid prepared abundantly before his death.
\v 6 ¶ Then hee called for Solomon his sonne, and charged him to build an house for the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel.
\v 7 And Dauid saide to Solomon; My sonne, as for me, it was in my mind to build an house vnto the Name of the \nd LORD\nd* my God.
\v 8 But the word of the \nd LORD\nd* came to mee, saying, \x + \xo 22:8 \xt Chap. 28.3. 2.sam. 7.13.\x*Thou hast shed blood abundantly, and hast made great warres: thou shalt not build an house vnto my Name, because thou hast shed much blood vpon the earth in my sight.
\v 9 Behold, a sonne shall bee borne to thee, who shall bee a man of rest, and I will giue him rest from all his enemies round about: for his name shalbe \f + \fr 22:9 \ft That is, peaceable.\f*Solomon, and I wil giue peace and quietnesse vnto Israel in his dayes.
\v 10 Hee shall build an house for my Name, and he shal be my sonne, and I \add will be\add* his father, and I will establish the throne of his kingdome ouer Israel for euer.
\v 11 Now my sonne, The \nd LORD\nd* be with thee, and prosper thou, and build the house of the \nd LORD\nd* thy God, as he hath said of thee.
\v 12 Onely the \nd LORD\nd* giue thee wisedome and vnderstanding, and giue thee charge concerning Israel, that thou mayest keepe the Law of the \nd LORD\nd* thy God.
\v 13 Then shalt thou prosper, if thou takest heed to fulfill the Statutes and Iudgements which the \nd LORD\nd* charged Moses with, concerning Israel: be strong, and of good courage, dread not, nor be dismayed.
\v 14 Now beholde, \f + \fr 22:14 \ft Or, in my pouertie.\f*in my trouble I haue prepared for the house of the \nd LORD\nd* an hundred thousand talents of gold, and a thousand thousand talents of siluer, and of brasse and yron without \x + \xo 22:14 \xt As Ver.3.\x*weight: (for it is in abundance) timber also and stone haue I prepared, and thou mayest adde thereto.
\v 15 Moreouer, \add there are\add* workmen with thee in abundance, hewers, and \f + \fr 22:15 \ft That is, Masons and Carpenters.\f*workers of stone and timber, and all maner of cunning men for euery maner of worke:
\v 16 Of the gold, the siluer, and the brasse, and the yron, \add there is\add* no number. Arise \add therefore\add*, and be doing, and the \nd LORD\nd* be with thee.
\v 17 ¶ Dauid also commanded all the Princes of Israel to helpe Solomon his sonne, \add saying\add*,
\v 18 \add Is\add* \add not\add* the \nd LORD\nd* your God with you? and hath he not giuen you rest on euery side? for he hath giuen the inhabitants of the land into mine hand, and the land is subdued before the \nd LORD\nd*, and before his people.
\v 19 Now set your heart and your soule to seeke the \nd LORD\nd* your God: arise therfore, and build ye the Sanctuary of the \nd LORD\nd* God, to bring the Arke of the Couenant of the \nd LORD\nd*, & the holy vessels of God, into the house that is to be built to the Name of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\c 23
\iex 1 Dauid in his old age maketh Solomon King. 2 The number and distribution of the Leuites 7 The families of the Gershonites. 12 The sonnes of Kohath. 21 The sonnes of Merari. 24 The office of the Leuites.
\v 1 ¶ So \x + \xo 23:1 \xt Chap. 28.5.\x*when Dauid was old and full of dayes, he made Solomon his sonne king ouer Israel.
\v 2 ¶ And he gathered together all the Princes of Israel, with the Priests and the Leuites.
\v 3 Now the Leuites were numbred from the age of thirtie \x + \xo 23:3 \xt Num. 4.3.\x*yeeres and vpward: and their number, by their polles, man by man, was thirtie and eight thousand.
\v 4 Of which, twentie and foure thousand \add were\add* \f + \fr 23:4 \ft Or, to ouersee.\f*to set forward the work of the house of the \nd LORD\nd*: and sixe thousand \add were\add* Officers and Iudges.
\v 5 Moreouer, foure thousand \add were\add* porters, and foure thousand praised the \nd LORD\nd* with the instruments which I made (\add said Dauid\add*) to praise \add therewith\add*.
\v 6 And \x + \xo 23:6 \xt Exod. 6.16, 1.chro. 6.1. &c., 2.chro. 8.14. and 29.25.\x*Dauid diuided them into \f + \fr 23:6 \ft Heb. diuisions.\f*courses among the sonnes of Leui, \add namely\add* Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.
\v 7 ¶ Of the \x + \xo 23:7 \xt Chap. 26.21.\x*Gershonites \add were\add* \f + \fr 23:7 \ft Or, Libni, \xt chap. 6.17.\f*Laadan, and Shimei.
\v 8 The sonnes of Laadan, the chiefe \add was\add* Iehiel, and Zetham, and Ioel, three.
\v 9 The sonnes of Shimei: Shelomith, and Haziel, and Haran, three. These \add were\add* the chiefe of the fathers of Laadan.
\v 10 And the sonnes of Shimei \add were\add*: Iahath, \f + \fr 23:10 \ft Or, Ziza, \xt ver.11.\f*Zina, and Ieush, and Beriah. These foure \add were\add* the sonnes of Shimei.
\v 11 And Iahath was the chiefe, and Ziza the second: but Ieush and Beriah \f + \fr 23:11 \ft Heb. did not multiply sonnes.\f*had not many sonnes: therefore they were in one reckoning, according to \add their\add* fathers house.
\v 12 ¶ The sonnes of Kohath: Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, foure.
\v 13 The sonnes of \x + \xo 23:13 \xt Exo. 6.20.\x*Amram: Aaron and Moses: and \x + \xo 23:13 \xt Exod. 28. Heb. 5.4.\x*Aaron was separated, that he should sanctifie the most holy things, he and his sonnes for euer, to burne incense before the \nd LORD\nd*, to minister vnto him, and to blesse in his Name for euer.
\v 14 \x + \xo 23:14 \xt Exo. 2.22.\x*Now \add concerning\add* Moses the man of God, his sonnes were named of the tribe of Leui.
\v 15 The sonnes of Moses \add were\add*: \x + \xo 23:15 \xt Exo. 18.3,4.\x*Gershom and Eliezer.
\v 16 Of the sonnes of Gershom Shebuel \add was\add* the chiefe.
\v 17 And the sonnes of Eliezer \add were\add*: \x + \xo 23:17 \xt Chap. 26.25.\x*Rehabiah \f + \fr 23:17 \ft Or, the first\f*the chiefe. And Eliezer had none other sonnes: but the sonnes of Rehabiah \f + \fr 23:17 \ft Heb. were highly multiplied.\f*were very many.
\v 18 Of the sonnes of Izhar, Shelomith the chiefe.
\v 19 Of the sonnes of Hebron, Ieriah the first, Amariah the second, Iahaziel the third, and Iekamiam the fourth.
\v 20 Of the sonnes of Uzziel: Michah the first, and Iesiah the second.
\v 21 ¶ The sonnes of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. The sonnes of Mahli: Eleazar and Kish.
\v 22 And Eleazar died, and had no sonnes but daughters: and their \f + \fr 23:22 \ft Or, kinsemen.\f*brethren the sonnes of Kish tooke them.
\v 23 The sonnes of Mushi: Mahli, and Eder, and Ierimoth, three.
\v 24 ¶ These \add were\add* the sonnes of \x + \xo 23:24 \xt Num. 10.24.\x*Leui after the house of their fathers, \add euen\add* the chiefe of the fathers, as they were counted by number of names by their polles, that did the worke for the seruice of the house of the \nd LORD\nd*, from the age of \x + \xo 23:24 \xt Num. 1.3.\x*twentie yeeres and vpward.
\v 25 For Dauid sayd, The \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel hath giuen rest vnto his people, \f + \fr 23:25 \ft Or, and he dwelleth in Ierusalem, &c.\f*that they may dwell in Ierusalem for euer.
\v 26 And also vnto the Leuites: they shall no \add more\add* cary the Tabernacle, nor any vessels of it for the seruice thereof.
\v 27 For by the last words of Dauid, the Leuites \add were\add* \f + \fr 23:27 \ft Heb. number.\f*numbred from twentie yeeres olde, and aboue:
\v 28 Because \f + \fr 23:28 \ft Heb. their station was at the hand of the sonnes of Aaron.\f*their office \add was\add* to wait on the sonnes of Aaron, for the seruice of the house of the \nd LORD\nd*, in the courts, and in the chambers, and in the purifying of all holy things, and the worke of the seruice of the house of God:
\v 29 Both for the \x + \xo 23:29 \xt Chap. 9.29, &c. leuit. 6.21.\x*shew-bread, and for the fine floure for meat offering, and for the vnleauened cakes, and for \add that which is baked in\add* the \f + \fr 23:29 \ft Or, flat plate.\f*panne, and for that which is fried, and for all maner of measures and size:
\v 30 And to stand euery morning to thanke and praise the \nd LORD\nd*, and likewise at Euen:
\v 31 And to offer all burnt sacrifices vnto the \nd LORD\nd* in the Sabbaths, in the new moones, and on the set feasts, by number, according to the order commanded vnto them continually before the \nd LORD\nd*:
\v 32 And that they should keepe the charge of the Tabernacle of the Congregation, and the charge of the holy \add place\add*, and the charge of the sonnes of Aaron their brethren, in the seruice of the house of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\c 24
\iex 1 The diuisions of the sonnes of Aaron by lot into foure and twenty orders. 20 The Kohathites, 27 and the Merarites diuided by lot.
\v 1 ¶ Now \add these are\add* the diuisions of the sonnes of Aaron. \x + \xo 24:1 \xt Leui. 10.4.\x*The sonnes of Aaron: Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.
\v 2 But Nadab and Abihu died \x + \xo 24:2 \xt Num. 3.4. and 26.60.\x*before their father, and had no children: Therefore Eleazar and Ithamar executed the Priests office.
\v 3 And Dauid distributed them, both Zadok of the sonnes of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sonnes of Ithamar, according to their offices in their seruice.
\v 4 And there were moe chiefe men found of the sonnes of Eleazar, then of the sonnes of Ithamar: and \add thus\add* were they diuided. Among the sonnes of Eleazar \add there were\add* sixteene chiefe men of the house of \add their\add* fathers, and eight among the sonnes of Ithamar according to the house of their fathers.
\v 5 Thus were they diuided by lot, one sort with another; for the gouernours of the Sanctuarie, and gouernours \add of the house\add* of God, were of the sonnes of Eleazar, and of the sonnes of Ithamar.
\v 6 And Shemaiah the sonne of Nathanael the Scribe, \add one\add* of the Leuites, wrote them \add before\add* the King and the Princes, and Zadok the Priest, and Ahimelech the sonne of Abiathar, and before the chiefe of the fathers of the priests and Leuites: \add one\add* \f + \fr 24:6 \ft Heb. house of the father\f*principall houshold being taken for Eleazar, and one taken for Ithamar.
\v 7 Now the first lot came foorth to Iehoiarib: the second to Iedaiah,
\v 8 The third to Harim, the fourth to Seorim,
\v 9 The fifth to Malchiiah, the sixth to Miiamin,
\v 10 The seuenth to Hakkoz, the eight to \x + \xo 24:10 \xt Luk. 1.5.\x*Abiiah,
\v 11 The ninth to Ieshua, the tenth to Shecaniah,
\v 12 The eleuenth to Eliashib, the twelfth to Iakim,
\v 13 The thirteenth to Huppah, the fourteenth to Ieshebeab,
\v 14 The fifteenth to Bilgah, the sixteenth to Immer,
\v 15 The seuenteenth to Hezir, the eighteenth to Aphses,
\v 16 The ninteenth to Pethahiah, the twentieth to Iehezekel,
\v 17 The one and twentieth to Iachin, the two and twentieth to Gamul,
\v 18 The three and twentieth to Delaiah, the foure and twentieth to Maaziah.
\v 19 These \add were\add* the orderings of them in their seruice to come into the house of the \nd LORD\nd* according to their maner, vnder Aaron their father, as the \nd LORD\nd* God of Israel had commanded him.
\v 20 ¶ And the rest of the sonnes of Leui \add were these\add*: of the sons of Amram, Shubael: of the sonnes of Shubael, Iedeiah.
\v 21 Concerning Rehabiah, of the sons of Rehabiah, the first \add was\add* Isshiah.
\v 22 Of the Izharites, Shelomoth: of the sonnes of Shelomoth, Iahath.
\v 23 And the sonnes \add of \x + \xo 24:23 \xt Chap. 23.19. and 26.31.\x*Hebron\add*, Ieriah \add the first\add*, Amariah the second, Iahaziel the third, Iekameam the fourth.
\v 24 \add Of\add* the sonnes of Uzziel, Michah: of the sonnes of Michah, Shamir.
\v 25 The brother of Michah \add was\add* Isshiah: of the sonnes of Isshiah, Zechariah.
\v 26 The sonnes of Merari \add were\add* Mahli and Mushi: the sonnes of Iaaziah, Beno.
\v 27 ¶ The sonnes of Merari by Iaaziah, Beno, and Shoham, and Zaccur, and Ibri.
\v 28 Of Mahli \add came\add* Eleazar, who had no sonnes.
\v 29 Concerning Kish: the sonne of Kish \add was\add* Ierahmeel.
\v 30 The sonnes also of Mushi, Mahli, and Eder, and Ierimoth. These \add were\add* the sonnes of the Leuites after the house of their fathers.
\v 31 These likewise cast lots ouer against their brethren the sonnes of Aaron, in the presence of Dauid the King, and Zadok and Ahimelech, and the chiefe of the fathers of the priests and Leuites, euen the principall fathers ouer against their yonger brethren.
\c 25
\iex 1 The number & offices of the singers. 8 Their diuision by lot, into foure and twentie orders.
\v 1 ¶ Moreouer Dauid and the captaines of the hoste separated to the seruice of the sonnes of Asaph, and of Heman, and of Ieduthun, who should prophesie with harps, with psalteries, and with cymbals: and the number of the workmen, according to their seruice, was:
\v 2 Of the sonnes of Asaph: Zaccur, and Ioseph, and Nethaniah, and \f + \fr 25:2 \ft Otherwise called Iesharelah, \xt v.14.\f*Asarelah, the sonnes of Asaph vnder the hands of Asaph, which prophesied \f + \fr 25:2 \ft Heb. by the hand of the king.\f*according to the order of the king.
\v 3 Of Ieduthun: the sonnes of Ieduthun, Gedaliah, and \f + \fr 25:3 \ft Or, Izri, \xt ver.11.\f*Zeri, and Ieshaiah, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, \f + \fr 25:3 \ft With Shimei mentioned \xt ver. 17.\f*sixe, vnder the handes of their father Ieduthun, who prophesied with a harpe, to giue thankes and to praise the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 4 Of Heman: the sonnes of Heman, Bukkiah, Mattaniah, \f + \fr 25:4 \ft Or, Azareel, \xt ver. 18.\f*Uzziel, \f + \fr 25:4 \ft Or, Shubael, \xt ver. 20.\f*Shebuel, and Ierimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliatha, Giddalti, and Romamti-Ezer, Ioshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, \add and\add* Mahazioth:
\v 5 All these \add were\add* the sonnes of Heman the kings Seer in the \f + \fr 25:5 \ft Or, matters.\f*wordes of God, to lift vp the horne. And God gaue to Heman fourteene sonnes and three daughters.
\v 6 All these \add were\add* vnder the hands of their father, for song \add in\add* the house of the \nd LORD\nd* with cymbals, psalteries and harpes, for the seruice of the house of God, \f + \fr 25:6 \ft Heb. by the hands of the King.\f*according to the kings order, to Asaph, Ieduthun, and Heman.
\v 7 So the number of them, with their brethren that were instructed in the songs of the \nd LORD\nd*, \add euen\add* all that were cunning, was two hundred, foure score and eight.
\v 8 ¶ And they cast lots ward against \add ward\add*, as well the small as the great, the teacher as the scholler.
\v 9 Now the first lot came foorth for Asaph to Ioseph, the second to Gedaliah, who with his brethren and sonnes \add were\add* twelue:
\v 10 The third to Zaccur, \add he\add*, his sons, and his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 11 The fourth to Izri, \add he\add*, his sonnes and his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 12 The fift to Nethaniah, hee, his sonnes and his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 13 The sixt to Bukkiah, \add he\add*, his sons and his brethren \add were\add* twelue.
\v 14 The seuenth to Iesharelah, hee, his sonnes & his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 15 The eight to Ieshaiah, hee, his sonnes and his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 16 The ninth to Mattaniah, \add he\add*, his sonnes and his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 17 The tenth to Shimei, \add he\add*, his sons and his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 18 The eleuenth to Azareel, hee, his sonnes and his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 19 The twelfth to Hashabiah, \add he\add*, his sonnes and his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 20 The thirteenth to Shubael, hee, his sonnes and his brethren \add were\add* twelue:
\v 21 The fourteenth to Mattithiah, hee, his sonnes and his brethren, \add were\add* twelue.
\v 22 The fifteenth to Ierimoth, hee, his sonnes & his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 23 The sixteenth to Hananiah, hee, his sonnes & his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 24 The seuenteenth to Ioshbekashah, \add he\add*, his sonnes and his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 25 The eighteenth to Hanani: hee, his sonnes & his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 26 The nineteenth to Mallothi, hee, his sonnes & his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 27 The twentieth to Eliathah, hee, his sonnes & his brethren, \add were\add* twelue:
\v 28 The one and twentieth to Hothir, \add he\add*, his sonnes and his brethren \add were\add* twelue.
\v 29 The two and twentieth to Giddalti, hee, his sonnes and his brethren, \add were\add* twelue.
\v 30 The three and twentieth to Mahazioth, \add he\add*, his sonnes and his brethren, \add were\add* twelue.
\v 31 The foure and twentieth to Romamti-Ezer, \add he\add*, his sonnes and his brethren, \add were\add* twelue.
\c 26
\iex 1 The diuisions of the porters. 13 The gates assigned by lot. 20 The Leuites that had charge of the treasures. 29 Officers and Iudges.
\v 1 ¶ Concerning the diuisions of the porters: of the Korhites \add was\add* \f + \fr 26:1 \ft Or, Shelemiah, \xt ver. 14.\f*Meshelemiah the sonne of Kore, of the sonnes of \f + \fr 26:1 \ft Or, Abiasaph, \xt chap. 9.19. & 6.37.\f*Asaph.
\v 2 And the sonnes of Meshelemiah \add were\add* Zechariah the first borne, Iediael the second, Zebadiah the third, Iathniel the fourth,
\v 3 Elam the fifth, Iehohanan the sixth, Elioenai the seuenth.
\v 4 Moreouer the sonnes of Obed-Edom \add were\add* Shemaiah the first borne, Iehozabad the second, Ioah the thirde, and Sacar the fourth, and Nethaneel the fifth.
\v 5 Ammiel the sixth, Issachar the seuenth, Peulthai the eighth: for God blessed \f + \fr 26:5 \ft That is, Obed-Edom, as \xt chap. 13.14.\f*him.
\v 6 Also vnto Shemaiah his sonne were sonnes borne, that ruled throughout the house of their father: for they \add were\add* mighty men of valour.
\v 7 The sonnes of Shemaiah: Othni, and Rephael, and Obed, Elzabad, whose brethren \add were\add* strong men; Elihu, and Semachiah.
\v 8 All these of the sonnes of Obed-Edom: they and their sonnes and their brethren, able men for strength for the seruice, \add were\add* threescore and two of Obed-Edom.
\v 9 And Meshelemiah had sonnes and brethren, strong men, eighteene.
\v 10 Also Hosah of the children of Merari, had sonnes: Simri the chiefe, (for \add though\add* he was not the first borne, yet his father made him the chiefe)
\v 11 Hilkiah the second, Tebaliah the thirde, Zechariah the fourth: all the sonnes and brethren of Hosah, \add were\add* thirteene.
\v 12 Among these \add were\add* the diuisions of the porters, \add euen\add* among the chiefe men, \add hauing\add* wards one against another, to minister in the house of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 13 ¶ And they cast lots \f + \fr 26:13 \ft Or, aswel for the smal as for the great.\f*as well the small as the great, according to the house of their fathers for euery gate.
\v 14 And the lot Eastward fel to \f + \fr 26:14 \ft Called Meshelemiah, \xt ver. 1.\f*Shelemiah; then for Zechariah his sonne (a wise counseller:) they cast lots, and his lot came out Northward.
\v 15 To Obed-Edom Southward, and to his sonnes, the house of \f + \fr 26:15 \ft Hebr. gatherings.\f*Asuppim.
\v 16 To Shuppim and Hosa, the lot came foorth Westward with the gate Shallecheth, by the causey of the going \f + \fr 26:16 \ft See \xt 1.King 10.4. 2.chr. 9.4,11.\f*vp, ward against ward.
