\v 18 And Parbar Westward, foure at the causey, \add and\add* two at Parbar.
\v 19 These \add are\add* the diuisions of the porters among the sonnes of Kore, and among the sonnes of Merari.
\v 20 ¶ And of the Leuites, Ahiiah \add was\add* ouer the treasures of the house of God, and ouer the treasures of the \f + \fr 26:20 \ft Heb, holy things.\f*dedicate things.
\v 21 \add As concerning\add* the sonnes of \f + \fr 26:21 \ft Or, Libni, \xt chap. 6.17.\f*Laadan: the sonnes of the Gershonite Laadan, hiefe fathers; \add euen\add* of Laadan the Gershonite, \add were\add* \f + \fr 26:21 \ft Or, Iehiel, \xt chap. 23.8.\f*Iehieli.
\v 22 The sonnes of Iehieli, Zetham and Ioel his brother, \add which were\add* ouer the treasures of the house of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 23 Of the Amramites, \add and\add* the Izharites, the Hebronites, \add and\add* the Uzzielites:
\v 24 And Shebuel the sonne of Gershom, the sonne of Moses, \add was\add* ruler of the treasures.
\v 25 And his brethren by Eliezer: Rehabiah his sonne, and Ieshaiah his sonne, and Ioram his sonne, and Zichri his sonne, & Shelomith his sonne.
\v 26 Which Shelomith and his brethren, \add were\add* ouer all the treasures of the dedicate things, which Dauid the king and the chiefe fathers, the captaines ouer thousands and hundreds, and the captaines of the hoste had dedicated.
\v 27 \f + \fr 26:27 \ft Heb. out of the battels and spoiles.\f*Out of the spoyles wonne in battels, did they dedicate to maintaine the house of the \nd LORD\nd*.
\v 28 And all that Samuel the Seer, and Saul the sonne of Kish, and Abner the sonne of Ner, and Ioab the sonne of Zeruiah had dedicated, \add and\add* whosoeuer had dedicated \add any thing, it was\add* vnder the hand of Shelomith and of his brethren.
\v 29 ¶ Of the Izharites, Chenaniah and his sonnes, \add were\add* for the outward busines ouer Israel, for officers and Iudges.
